results.description:
Chapter 5 in my continuing behavior series
Photo 1:  Checking To See If The Squirrel Is Still There
I walked to the middle of the street once the squirrel left to photograph the vulture on my neighbor's roof.  At first it was looking in the direction where the squirrel had been approaching.  
Photo 2:  Turkey Vulture Basking In The Sun
Once it was satisfied the squirrel was gone, it seemed to be enjoying the warm sunshine.  It was amazing to me how big some of the wing feathers are.
Photo 3:  Time For A Nice Feather Rouse
It seemed to be looking at me as it started to rouse.  A rouse is when a bird raises all their feathers then gives them a shake.  Must have felt safe and relaxed in the sunshine on the roof.
Photo 4:  Someone Needs Head & Shoulders
This was a first.  When it was in full rouse, there seemed to be dandruff flying everywhere.  I've seen a lot of bird rouses but never seen flying specks.  
Photo 5:  Turkey Vulture Yawn
A big yawn is always nice after a good rouse.  
Photo 6:  Gazing Longingly At Its Meal
After the rouse and yawn, the vulture walked to the edge of the roof and peered at the dead squirrel.  It acted like it was still hungry and wanted to return to its meal, but there I was in the middle of the street by the squirrel.

Chapt 1 can be seen here:  https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/9068504
Chpt 2:  https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/9081559
Chpt 3:  https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/9092844
Chpt 4:  https://www.inaturalist.org/observations/9102853
